    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3660950486" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3660950486" />
    <a title="Ron" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1256262-ron"><img alt="Ron" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442983573p2/1256262.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3660950486?book_show_action=true">Nov 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ron" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ron" href="/user/show/1256262-ron">Ron</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/34465799-borders-of-infinity">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1256262-ron?shelf=award-finalist">award-finalist</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1256262-ron?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1256262-ron?shelf=anthology">anthology</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1256262-ron?shelf=ebook">ebook</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3660950486" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer346665750032094439">“I hope you are not going to make a habit of returning from your mission assignments on a stretcher.”<br/><br/>A collection of three Miles Vorkasigan novellas with a framing story. The usual wit and wisdom of Bujold. I’d read all of them before. Nothing wrong with the stories nor the approach. Fine if you’re a die-hard Bujold or Miles fan.<br/><br/>“Dealing with Suegar, Miles decided, was like fencing in a hall of mirrors. Your target, though real, was never quite where it looked as though it should be.”<br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

