              <span id="reviewTextContainer4056014249" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18276348974099232463">3.5 It certainly continues to be formulaic but the formula is fun and the characters are certainly a strong point for Bujold. It’s sometimes annoying to be in Miles’ somewhat too hormonal head but the action and the world tends to make up for it. This one was particularly odd as it is a collection of novellas so the chronology is definitely confusing but in many ways, that’s somewhat secondary for these books. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


